What I suggested had come to an end was not the occurrence of events, even =
large and grave events, but History: that is, history understood as a singl=
e, coherent, evolutionary process, when taking into account the experience =
of all peoples in all times=E2=80=A6Both Hegel and Marx believed that the e=
